headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 24 points, Derrick White had 22 and the Boston Celtics extended their winning streak to six games by beating the Toronto Raptors 111-101 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 24 points as Celtics extend winning streak to six games, beat Raptors 111-101

headlines.description: — Ty Jerome scored 20 points in 21 minutes, and the Cleveland Cavaliers routed the Orlando Magic 122-82 on Tuesday night for their eighth consecutive win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers rout Magic 122-82 for their 8th straight win

headlines.description: — Jalen Green had 25 points and Alperen Sengun added 23 to lead the Houston Rockets to a 100-97 win over the Milwaukee Bucks on Tuesday night in a game where Amen Thompson was ejected for a hard foul on Giannis Antetokounmpo.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green has 25 points as Houston Rockets hold on for 100-97 win over Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 29 points and eight assists, his final one a feed to Jaylen Wells for a dunk with 9.1 seconds left in overtime, and the Memphis Grizzlies closed the extra period with a 7-0 run to beat the Phoenix Suns 151-148 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant helps the Grizzlies outlast the Suns 151-148 in overtime

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Trey Murphy III scored 24 points, Zion Williamson added 18 and the New Orleans Pelicans completed a two-game home game sweep of the San Antonio Spurs, 109-103 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trey Murphy III scores 24 points, Zion Williamson adds 18 and the Pelicans beat the Spurs 109-103

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry and Draymond Green scored 15 points each and the Golden State Warriors joined an elite group with their 3,000th franchise victory on Tuesday night, 128-92 over the Charlotte Hornets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors thump Hornets 128-92 for franchise's 3,000th win

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 19 points, 15 rebounds and 12 assists in his first game against the Dallas Mavericks since they traded him to the Lakers, leading Los Angeles to a 107-99 victory Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic posts a triple-double against the Dallas Mavericks, leads the Lakers to a 107-99 win
